replies.bodyText:
@rjernst I have updated the setting handling. Now new breakers are affix settings. The initial breaker settings are still provided by the plugin, but facilities are in place to make that as seamless as possible.
Still an open question around making the current circuit breakers affix settings and deprecating their current setting values.
Also, I opted to NOT make durability configurable. This seems like something a user should NEVER be able to change (even at start up time).

@rjernst volatile reads are 3x as slow as non-volatile. But, given the other changes, I think it will be OK (we won't need concurrent hash map any longer).
I am going to work on implementing this (initializing via ctor, volatile settings, etc.) and test performance with JMH. Will get back once done.
Thanks so much for your thoughts and time on this!

